# CLAUDE.md — Minecraft Plugin Dev with Tiered Visual Debugging

## Project
This is a Minecraft plugin project. Built with [Maven/Gradle].

## Visual Debug Skill
Located at: `~/mc-visual-debug-skill`

**Before any build/test cycle, read the skill:**
```
cat ~/mc-visual-debug-skill/SKILL.md
```

## Two Scripts

| Script | Purpose |
|--------|---------|
| `~/mc-visual-debug-skill/scripts/mc_helper.py` | Build, deploy, server, client, input |
| `~/mc-visual-debug-skill/scripts/observe.py` | Tiered observation engine |

## Build → Deploy → Restart

```bash
python ~/mc-visual-debug-skill/scripts/mc_helper.py full-cycle
```

Or manually:
```bash
python ~/mc-visual-debug-skill/scripts/mc_helper.py build
python ~/mc-visual-debug-skill/scripts/mc_helper.py deploy
python ~/mc-visual-debug-skill/scripts/mc_helper.py server-restart
python ~/mc-visual-debug-skill/scripts/mc_helper.py server-wait-ready
```

## Launch Client (first time or if closed)
```bash
python ~/mc-visual-debug-skill/scripts/mc_helper.py client-launch
```

## Send In-Game Input
```bash
python ~/mc-visual-debug-skill/scripts/mc_helper.py chat "/your-command"
python ~/mc-visual-debug-skill/scripts/mc_helper.py key "w" --duration 2
python ~/mc-visual-debug-skill/scripts/mc_helper.py click 400 300
```

## Observe — Pick the Right Tier!

**Always start at Tier 0 and escalate only if needed.**

```bash
# Tier 0 — Server logs (ALWAYS do this first, it's free)
python ~/mc-visual-debug-skill/scripts/observe.py logs --tail 30

# Tier 1 — Chat OCR (after /commands, reads chat text cheaply)
python ~/mc-visual-debug-skill/scripts/observe.py chat-ocr

# Tier 2 — Smart screenshot (only sends image if screen changed)
python ~/mc-visual-debug-skill/scripts/observe.py screenshot

# Tier 3 — Burst capture (for particles, spawns, transient effects)
python ~/mc-visual-debug-skill/scripts/observe.py burst --frames 5 --duration 2

# Tier 4 — Video keyframes (for animations, movement, complex sequences)
python ~/mc-visual-debug-skill/scripts/observe.py record --duration 5
```

## Tier Selection Guide

| Question to answer | Use tier |
|---|---|
| "Did the server throw an error?" | 0 (logs) |
| "What did the /command respond?" | 1 (chat-ocr) |
| "Did the GUI/world change?" | 2 (screenshot) |
| "Did particles/entities appear briefly?" | 3 (burst) |
| "Did the animation/movement work?" | 4 (record) |

## Review Past Observations
```bash
python ~/mc-visual-debug-skill/scripts/observe.py buffer --last 10
```

## Testing Philosophy
1. Always check logs first (Tier 0) — catches 60%+ of issues for free.
2. Use chat OCR (Tier 1) before screenshots — 50 text tokens vs 250 image tokens.
3. Only escalate to visual tiers when text can't answer the question.
4. Wait 1-2 seconds between input and observation.
5. Combine tier results: logs + chat + visual = full picture.
